      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>,<strong> half </strong>the <strong>chopped ginger </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), the <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and <strong>garam masala </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the tomatoes have started to soften</p><p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5-6 min further or until the sauce has slightly thickened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
