      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grind the<strong> remaining garlic</strong> and <strong>remaining ginger</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> until you're left with a smooth paste, then transfer the paste to a mixing bowl</p><p>Add<strong> </strong>the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> to the paste and mix to combine – this is your <strong>coriander chutney</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
